# Documentation Sync on Commit

When features, configuration, architecture, providers, or CLI requirements change, **include implementation and documentation updates in the same commit**.

**Full policy:** [docs/DOCUMENTATION_POLICY.md](../../docs/DOCUMENTATION_POLICY.md) — audience, README shape, legacy, **P0/P1/P2 sync tiers**.

## Pre-commit Checklist

1. **README sync (P1 only):** When fork **entry/summary** changes, update both [README.md](../../README.md) and [README_ja.md](../../README_ja.md) summary sections (parallel headings). Progress-only changes → [FORK_STATUS.md](../../docs/FORK_STATUS.md) **and** [ja/FORK_STATUS.md](../../docs/ja/FORK_STATUS.md) (P0), not README body. Human doc pairs: [DOCUMENTATION_POLICY §4 B2b](../../docs/DOCUMENTATION_POLICY.md#b2b--human-docs-docsja-pairs). See [DOCUMENTATION_POLICY §7](../../docs/DOCUMENTATION_POLICY.md#7-commit-sync-tiers-e2).
2. **Navigation:** Add new **active** docs to [DOCUMENTATION_INDEX.md](../../docs/DOCUMENTATION_INDEX.md). AGENTS.md link row only if needed (skeleton). Details → [docs/agents/](../../docs/agents/). Do not edit stub files under `docs/claude-*.md`.
3. **Proposals:** If customer-facing content changes, update `docs/proposals/` and `scripts/pptx-gen/slide-data.mjs` (regenerate PPTX if needed)
4. **ADR:** Record design decisions in [docs/decisions/](../../docs/decisions/)

## What to Update

| Change | Minimum docs to update |
|--------|------------------------|
| LLM / CLI provider | [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) (summary only), [docs/agents/development-notes.md](../../docs/agents/development-notes.md), [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md), README summaries if P1, relevant integration guide |
| OpenAI catalog / prompt guidance | [config/llm-model-catalog.json](../../config/llm-model-catalog.json), [docs/OPENAI_PROMPT_GUIDANCE.md](../../docs/OPENAI_PROMPT_GUIDANCE.md), [docs/decisions/TECH_STACK_LLM_MODEL_CATALOG.md](../../docs/decisions/TECH_STACK_LLM_MODEL_CATALOG.md), README summaries if P1 |
| API / endpoints | [docs/API_REFERENCE.md](../../docs/API_REFERENCE.md), [docs/DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md](../../docs/DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md) |
| Security policy | [docs/SECURITY.md](../../docs/SECURITY.md), [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) |
| Wall-Bounce behavior | [docs/WALL_BOUNCE_SYSTEM.md](../../docs/WALL_BOUNCE_SYSTEM.md), related ADR |
| Tech stack | [docs/TECH_STACK_WORKSPACE.md](../../docs/TECH_STACK_WORKSPACE.md), [docs/decisions/TECH_STACK_*.md](../../docs/decisions/), [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) |

## AGENTS.md Policy

- [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) is skeleton only (Quick Nav + Mandatory Rules summary + link table)
- [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md) is shim only — link to AGENTS.md; do not restore full rules there
- Put details in [docs/agents/commands.md](../../docs/agents/commands.md), [mcp-rules.md](../../docs/agents/mcp-rules.md), [development-notes.md](../../docs/agents/development-notes.md)

## Cursor Rules (`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`)

Thin hooks only — link to AGENTS.md / domain docs; do not duplicate constitution or catalog text.

| Rule | Scope |
|------|--------|
| [wall-bounce-constitution.mdc](./wall-bounce-constitution.mdc) | `alwaysApply` — constitution summary + links |
| [documentation-sync.mdc](./documentation-sync.mdc) | `alwaysApply` — commit checklist |
| [llm-catalog-edits.mdc](./llm-catalog-edits.mdc) | globs: `config/llm-model-catalog.json`, schema |

## Logic Documentation Language

**Logic and rule docs MUST be written in English**, including:

- [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md), [docs/agents/*.md](../../docs/agents/)
- [docs/WALL_BOUNCE_SYSTEM.md](../../docs/WALL_BOUNCE_SYSTEM.md), [docs/ANTIGRAVITY_CLI_MIGRATION.md](../../docs/ANTIGRAVITY_CLI_MIGRATION.md)
- `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (agent rules)

Customer-facing proposals (`docs/proposals/`) and `README_ja.md` may remain in Japanese.

Do not split implementation-only and docs-only commits unless the user explicitly requests it — **one commit with implementation + docs**.

## Examples

```
# ✅ GOOD — same commit
feat: add codegen route to TaskRouter
  src/...
  docs/ARCHITECTURE.md
  README.md, README_ja.md

# ❌ BAD — README left stale
feat: Antigravity CLI support
  docs/ARCHITECTURE.md only, README not updated
```
